List of maintainers and how to submit changes
=============================================

Please try to follow the guidelines below. This will make things
easier on the maintainers. Not all of these guidelines matter for every
trivial patch so apply some common sense.

1.	Always test your changes, however small, on at least one target
	platform (QEMU is acceptable for initial testing).

2.	Make sure your changes compile correctly. Building with different
	configurations or for different architectures is helpful.

3.	When you are happy with a change, submit it to the maintainers
	for the affected areas.

4.	Make a patch available to the relevant maintainer in the list.
	Use 'git format-patch' and 'git send-email' if possible.

5.	Include CHANGELOG entries if appropriate.

6.	All contributions must be made under the GPLv3 license.

Descriptions of section entries:

	M: Mail: patch submission address (maintainer)
	R: Reviewer: handles review and feedback
	L: Mailing list for patches and discussions
	S: Status:
	   Supported:	Someone is paid to look after this
	   Maintained:	Someone looks after it
	   Odd Fixes:	Occasionally fixed
	   Orphan:	No current maintainer
	   Obsolete:	Old code, to be removed
	F: Files and directories with wildcard patterns
	X: Excluded files and directories

